exFAT ('''Ex'''tended '''F'''ile '''A'''llocation '''T'''able) is available to Gentoo Linux systems through a [[Filesystem in Userspace|FUSE]] module.

== Installation ==

=== Kernel ===

{{KernelBox|title=Enable support for <var>CONFIG_FUSE_FS</var>|1=
File systems  --->
   <*> FUSE (Filesystem in Userspace) support
}}

=== Emerge ===

Install the FUSE exfat package:

{{Emerge|sys-fs/fuse-exfat}}

For filesystem creation and manipulation beyond that of the {{c|mount}} command it is necessary to install the user space tool package:

{{Emerge|sys-fs/exfat-utils}}

== Usage ==

=== Invocation ===

exFAT creation:

{{RootCmd|mkfs.exfat|output=<pre>
mkexfatfs 1.2.1
Usage: mkfs.exfat [-i volume-id] [-n label] [-p partition-first-sector] [-s sectors-per-cluster] [-V] <device>
</pre>}}

exFAT mounting:

{{RootCmd|mount.exfat-fuse|output=<pre>
FUSE exfat 1.0.1
Usage: mount.exfat-fuse [-d] [-o options] [-v] <device> <dir>
</pre>}}

=== Mount ===

To mount an exFAT filesystem:

{{RootCmd|mount.exfat /dev/sde1 /mnt/flash}}

For more information on mounting see {{c|man mount.exfat-fuse}}.

=== Unmount ===

To umount, simply specify the mount point:

{{RootCmd|umount /mnt/flash}}

=== Example operations ===

To create an exFAT filesystem on a removable device present at {{Path|/dev/sde1}} with the label of "Flash":

{{RootCmd|mkfs.exfat -n Flash /dev/sde1}}

To check the integrity of an exFAT filesystem:

{{RootCmd|fsck.exfat /dev/sde1}}

== Removal ==

=== Unmerge ===

Remove the FUSE filesystem utilities:

{{Unmerge|sys-fs/fuse-exfat}}

If installed, uninstall the user space tools as well:

{{Unmerge|sys-fs/exfat-utils}}

